description: PM Modi and UK's new PM Starmer discuss early conclusion of a free trade agreement, emphasizing deepening cooperation in various areas. ​“Both leaders recalled the historic relations between the two countries and reaffirmed their commitment to further deepen and advance the Comprehensive Strategic Partnership between India and the UK,” an official statement said.
title: First call: PM Modi, Starmer agree to speed up FTA talks, strengthen ties

description: Nirmala Sitharaman presents Narendra Modi’s third term Budget on July 23, focusing on infrastructure, middle class, women, and farm sector. Boosted by RBI’s record dividend, the seventh budget also addresses inflation, jobs, with fiscal year targets and reforms. The parliamentary session runs July 22-August 12; the Economic Survey will be presented.
title: First Budget of Modi 3.0: July 23 Budget to focus on infrastructure, targeted spending

description: India's Project Zorawar light tank  is expected to be ready for induction into the Army by 2027. The light tank, developed by DRDO and private sector company L&T, will have to undergo a series of summer and winter trials, including in deserts and high-altitude areas, over the next two to three years before the entire acquisition, production and induction process can actually begin.
title: Eye on China, desi light tank Zorawar to be ready by 2027

description: Lisa Nandy, the only Indian-origin MP in the new cabinet, held the shadow foreign secretary role. This is a stark contrast to the cabinet Boris Johnson had formed in July 2019 which was the most diverse in British history. Meanwhile British Pakistani MP Shabana Mahmood, who has been strongly critical of the Indian govt over Kashmir, has been appointed justice secretary.
title: One PIO and one PoK-origin MP in Starmer's new cabinet
Seven Tory MPs are preparing leadership bids
Rahul Gandhi wishes new British PM Kier Starmer

description: Two soldiers lost their lives in separate gunfights in Kulgam, along with the deaths of four terrorists. Security forces are engaged in ongoing operations to combat terrorism in the region. Lance Naik Pradeep Naik of Army’s Para Commando unit was killed in Modergam village, while havildar Raj Kumar of 1 Rashtriya Rifles died in Frisal Chinnigam area, officials said. The two operations are ongoing, with some more terrorists believed to be trapped at both sites.
title: 4 terrorists, 2 soldiers killed in J&K twin operations
Biden's family tensions with White House staff boil over after debate fiasco: Report
Rahul Gandhi writes to Rishi Sunak after UK election results

description: Rahul Gandhi, the leader of the opposition in Lok Sabha, will visit Manipur on Monday to meet people affected by recent violence in various districts of the northeastern state. This visit marks Gandhi's third trip to the conflict-ridden state and his first as the leader of the opposition. State Congress president K Meghachandra confirmed that Gandhi will travel from Delhi to Silchar by flight and will then proceed to Jiribam district, where fresh violence occurred on June 6.
title: Rahul Gandhi to visit Manipur on July 8, meet victims in relief camps

description: Rahul Gandhi, the leader of the opposition in Lok Sabha, will visit Manipur on Monday to meet people affected by recent violence in various districts of the northeastern state. This visit marks Gandhi's third trip to the conflict-ridden state and his first as the leader of the opposition. State Congress president K Meghachandra confirmed that Gandhi will travel from Delhi to Silchar by flight and will then proceed to Jiribam district, where fresh violence occurred on June 6.
title: Rahul Gandhi to visit Manipur on June 8, meet victims of violence in relief camps

description: An inexperienced yet spirited Zimbabwe pulled off an upset of massive proportions when they stunned an Indian team brimming with an array of Next-Gen stars by 13 runs in the first T20I of the five-match series in Harare on Saturday. India, who were recently crowned champions in the T20 World Cup albeit with a different set of players, were expected to trot past an unfancied Zimbabwe and the script followed that line when the hosts were restricted to 115 for nine. But from there, Zimbabwe wrote their own narrative, reducing India to 28 for four in the Power Play and then eventually bowled them out for 102 in 19.5 overs.
title: 'Celebrations khatam nahi hui aur...': Fans unimpressed after India shock loss
13 killed in Israeli strike on Gaza school: Reports

description: Arshdeep Singh, the left-arm fast bowler from India, received a grand reception upon his return to his hometown of Chandigarh. His fans and loved ones celebrated his arrival with traditional bhangra dance, flower garlands, and a lively procession.
title: 'I want to play all formats but at the moment...': Arshdeep

description: Indian all-rounder Hardik Pandya, crucial in India's T20 World Cup win, expressed his joy after the Mumbai victory parade. Reflecting on his journey, he recalled celebrating India's 2007 win and now feeling surreal being part of the team winning after 13 years. He praised Mumbai's support, calling it a blessing. Pandya revealed to PM Modi that he remained calm during tough times, which made the victory sweeter. Despite IPL 2024 criticism, Pandya's performance proved his resilience and leadership.
title: ‘In 2011, I was…’: Hardik after victory parade in Mumbai

description: Canada Police believes that the gold stolen last year in Canada's biggest-ever gold heist must have gone to India and Dubai gold markets. Over 6,500 gold bars disappeared overseas after being stolen from an airport, the department believes. "We believe a large portion has gone overseas to markets that are flush with gold," lead investigator Det. Sgt. Mike Mavity said.
title: Gold stolen in Canada's biggest ever heist ended up in India, Dubai: Police

description: The Islamic New Year, also known as Hijri New Year or Arabic New Year, marks the beginning of the Islamic lunar calendar year. The Islamic or Hijri calendar holds immense significance for Muslims worldwide, as it dates back to the migration, known as "Hijra", of Prophet Muhammad from Mecca to Medina in 622 CE.
title: Islamic new year 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages, quotes & more to share

description: Sikandar Raza took 3 for 25 as Zimbabwe defeated India by 13 runs in the first T20I at the Harare Sports Club on Saturday, an early blow to the newly-crowned world champions in the five-game series. India chose to field and restricted Zimbabwe to 115 for nine in their 20 overs but were always struggling in their reply and were bowled out for 102 with Pakistan-born off-spinner Raza taking the key wicket of touring captain Shubman Gill (31).
title: 1st T20I: Unfancied Zimbabwe stun India by 13 runs

description: India wrist spinner Kuldeep Yadav expressed his feelings about India's victory in the T20 World Cup on Saturday. He described the experience as surreal and beyond belief. The triumph was particularly special for Yadav, who played a crucial role in the team's success throughout the tournament.
title: 'This experience is something which...': Kuldeep on T20 WC win
Rambling, gambling Biden insists he is fit to run in painful interview
'Pray for long life': PM Modi greets Dalai Lama on 89th birthday

description: The Food Safety and Standards Authority of India (FSSAI) has approved changes to the nutritional information labeling on packaged food items during its 44th meeting, chaired by Apurva Chandra. The amendments to the Food Safety and Standards (Labelling and Display) Regulations, 2020 will require total salt, sugar, and saturated fat content to be displayed in bold letters and larger font sizes on food product labels.
title: 'Bold letter, bigger font': Check out food safety body's new labelling rules

description: Amartya Sen expressed concerns about the implementation of new criminal laws without proper discussions and lack of novelty in the New Education Policy. He also commented on Hindutva politics being challenged in recent elections. ​"There has not been any evidence that any such wide-ranging talks had preceded before enacting this with all the stakeholders. Also in this vast country, the problems faced by a state like Manipur and another state, say Madhya Pradesh, cannot be the same," Sen told reporters at Santiniketan.
title: New criminal laws not a welcome change: Amartya Sen

description: Lieutenant Governor of Delhi, VK Saxena, on Saturday gave nod to a recommendation for a probe against jailed former Delhi minister and Aam Aadmi Party leader Satyendar Jain in a graft case under the Prevention of Corruption Act. The probe again Jain is related to CCTV installation in the city. Jain, who is already on jail in a money laundering case, is accused of receiving a bribe of Rs 7 crore in connection with a Rs 571 crore project for the installation of CCTVs in 70 assembly constituencies.
title: More trouble for AAP: Satyendar Jain to be probed in bribery case

description: The opposition INDIA bloc has stepped up its demands ahead of the Union Budget session set to begin on July 22, with TMC leader Derek O'Brien listing out specific requests for the NDA-led central government. The TMC leader and Rajya Sabha MP emphasized the need for smooth parliamentary operations and called for a deputy speaker post in Lok Sabha to be allocated to an MP from the INDIA bloc.
title: Ahead of Budget, INDIA bloc ups ante over LS deputy speaker post

description: The Wimbledon Centre Court erupted in applause as Sachin Tendulkar was hailed as a World Cup winner and the highest run-scorer in cricket history. The crowd warmly welcomed him, along with England cricketers Ben Stokes, Jos Buttler and Joe Root. The day's matches began with Cameron Norrie vs Alexander Zverev and included a women’s singles match between Ons Jabeur and Elina Svitolina. Later, Novak Djokovic aimed to match Roger Federer’s record of eight Wimbledon titles, and Iga Swiatek faced a distinctive opponent.
title: Watch: Wimbledon erupts in applause for Sachin Tendulkar
Hathras stampede: Cops hint at political funding link; main accused sent to judicial custody
'No political angle': Police on murder of BSP leader Armstrong in Chennai

description: In his first press conference after being elected as UK PM, Labour Party's Keir Starmer on Saturday said he was "not prepared" to continue with the previous Rishi Sunak-led Conservative government's Rwanda migrants deportation scheme.  The Rwanda plan, finalised in April 2022 under the leadership of former Prime Minister Boris Johnson, stipulates that individuals who entered the United Kingdom unlawfully after January 1, 2022, will be relocated to Rwanda, a country situated approximately 4,000 miles (6,400 km) from Britain.
title: In first big move, UK PM scraps Sunak's migrant deportation plan
Four-storey building collapses in Surat, many feared trapped

description: Riyan Parag's father Parag Das presented him with the India cap before the first T20I against Zimbabwe, marking a historic milestone as Riyan became the first male cricketer from Assam to represent India. This emotional moment followed India's recent T20 World Cup victory. Parag earned his maiden call-up after a stellar IPL 2024 season, where he scored 573 runs for Rajasthan Royals. Alongside Abhishek Sharma and Dhruv Jurel, Parag debuted at Harare Sports Club on July 6th.
title: Watch: Riyan Parag gets India debut cap from his father

description: Pakistan's T20 World Cup campaign ended in early elimination after defeats to the USA and India. Azam, despite scoring 122 runs in four games, faced criticism for his strike rate of 101.66. Mushtaq Ahmed defended Azam, likening him to Virat Kohli. The PCB plans strategic changes, consulting Jason Gillespie and Gary Kirsten for the ICC Champions Trophy. Before this, Pakistan will host Bangladesh and England for five Tests, tour Australia for a white-ball series, and visit South Africa for Tests and white-ball matches.
title: 'Virat bhi time leta hai, Rohit bhi...': Ex-Pak star defends Babar Azam

description: Former India coach Ravi Shastri launched a scathing attack on Michael Vaughan after the former England captain criticised the scheduling of the T20 World Cup and suggested that it favoured India.

description: Jailed leader Amritpal Singh, recently elected as an independent MP from Khadoor Sahib in Punjab, faces controversy over his alleged involvement in radical activities. His mother defends him against accusations of being a Khalistani supporter.
title: 'He is not ... ': What Amritpal's mother said after MP took oath

description: Devprakash Madhukar, the main accused in the Hathras stampede that killed 121 people, was arrested in Nazafgarh by Uttar Pradesh Police. The stampede occurred during a satsang event, which exceeded its permitted attendance. Organizers attempted to conceal the true number of attendees. Madhukar’s lawyer claims he surrendered while receiving treatment in Delhi. Authorities are investigating the event's funding sources.
title: Hathras stampede: Main accused Devprakash Madhukar arrested

description: The White House and BNO News denied Laura Loomer's claims of a medical emergency canceling Biden's Wisconsin July fundraiser, stating Biden arrived in Delaware smoothly. Forbes verified this via video. Loomer shared a motorcade screenshot and suggested a Secret Service ER room reservation for Biden's canceled Pennsylvania trip, raising doubts about her credibility.
title: Did Biden suffer 'medical emergency' on Air Force One? White House replies
PM Modi congratulates newly elected Iranian Prez Masoud Pezeshkian

description: The sacred Shiv Lingam at the Amarnath cave shrine has started melting due to a heatwave, despite the annual yatra commencing just over a week ago. Over 150,000 devotees have already visited the shrine located at 3,880 meters in Jammu and Kashmir. Severe heatwave conditions have gripped north and central India, including the region around the shrine.
title: Amarnath shrine's Shiva Lingam melting fast amid heatwave: Reports

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi spoke with newly elected UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer on Saturday following Starmer's assumption of office on Friday after the Labour Party secured 412 out of 650 parliamentary seats in the general election. They discussed working towards the long-pending India-UK Free Trade Agreement. Modi extended his congratulations to Starmer for the Labour Party's victory. Both leaders expressed commitment to enhancing bilateral relations and agreed to advance the Free Trade Agreement between India and the UK.
title: 'Committed to deepening ties': PM Modi speaks to UK PM Starmer

description: The Indian cricket team is back home and enjoying star treatment after the victory in the ICC T20 World Cup. In a facilitation event held at the Maharashtra assembly, chief minister Eknath Shinde announced a reward of Rs 11 crore for Team India. Now the opposition has questioned the cash reward asking 'what was the need'. "They gave such a huge sum to the Indian Cricket Team, what was the need? Team India played for the country and not themselves, this is why the streets were flooded to welcome them," Wadettiwar told news agency ANI.
title: Maha oppn leader questions Rs 11cr cash reward to Indian cricket team

description: Mayawati adviseD the poor and Dalits to follow Bhimrao Ambedkar's path instead of relying on Babas like Bhole Baba. "Rather, by following the path shown by Baba Saheb Dr. Bhimrao Ambedkar, they will have to take power in their own hands and change their own destiny, that is, they will have to join their party BSP, only then they can avoid incidents like Hathras in which 121 people died, which is very worrying," she said.
title: 'Follow Ambedkar not Babas': Mayawati's appeal to Dalits

description: Saroj Devi, the mother of India's Olympic gold medallist javelin-thrower Neeraj Chopra, has said she will prepare a special 'churma' for Prime Minister Narendra Modi after the PM expressed his desire to taste the home-made version of the delicacy during a recent conversation with Chopra ahead of the Paris Olympics beginning July 26.
title: Neeraj Chopra's mother responds to PM Modi's 'churma' request

description: Karni Sena will create a nationwide stir if the CBI does not file a complaint regarding Sushant Singh Rajput's death case. However, his lawyer says, "We really have no update"
title: Sushant Singh's death case: Karni Sena to protest if CBI doesn't probe

description: Cheetah Gamini was seen playing with her cubs, who also engaged in playful antics with each other. Gamini, a South African cheetah at Kuno National Park, birthed five cubs, boosting the cheetah count to 26. Union environment minister Bhupender Yadav captured this. Gamini, from Tswalu Kalahari Reserve, increased cubs tally to 13. Project Cheetah brought 8 Namibian and 12 South African cheetahs. In January, Namibian cheetah 'Jwala' birthed four cubs.
title: Watch: Cheetah Gamini, 5 cubs play in the rain at Kuno National Park

description: SpaceX's Polaris Dawn mission is aiming to break space exploration records by sending astronauts to an orbital altitude of 870 miles, surpassing past missions since the 1970s. The crew will conduct various experiments, including the first commercial spacewalk, to study the effects of space travel on human health.
title: Elon Musk’s SpaceX sets new records with Polaris Dawn mission

description: Rahul Gandhi, addressing Congress workers in Ahmedabad, vowed to defeat Prime Minister Narendra Modi and the BJP in Gujarat, drawing parallels to their success in Ayodhya. He criticized BJP policies in Ayodhya, citing land disputes over the airport and grievances over Ram Temple inauguration exclusions. Gandhi alleged BJP vandalism and attacks on Congress offices, urging resilience. He planned visits to console families affected by recent tragedies in Gujarat and addressed arrests following clashes, emphasizing solidarity with affected Congress members and highlighting ongoing legal developments.

description: The scenes at the victory parade at Mumbai's Marine Drive en route to the Wankhede Stadium left the players overwhelmed by the love showered on them by the fans, who did everything they could to get a glimpse of their favourite players, which included this fan who climbed up a tree to get as close as posisble to the team's open-top bus that passed by.
title: T20 WC victory parade: What the fan on the tree saw

description: Congress criticized the government over NEET-UG counselling delay. Jairam Ramesh condemned the 'non-biological PM' and Education Minister's insensitivity. The Supreme Court, led by CJI Chandrachud and Justices Pardiwala and Misra, rejected deferment of NEET-UG 2024 despite irregularities, issuing notices to the Centre and NTA. Fresh decisions are awaited after the July 8 hearing.

description: CBI’s probe excluding Delhi CM Kejriwal saw new post-June 4 developments. SC briefed, chargesheet by July 3, 2024 assured per Solicitor General's submissions. Special Judge Baweja extended Sisodia’s custody till July 15, 2024. Kavitha case deferred to July 8. Sisodia to sign MLA funds docs. CBI’s incorrect status report contradicted earlier judicial order.

description: While much attention has been focused on Keir's historic victory, less is known about his wife, Victoria, who maintained a relatively low profile during the election campaign. The couple, both lawyers by training, married in 2007, a year before Starmer became Director of Public Prosecutions.
title: Who is Victoria Starmer? Low-profile wife of UK PM

description: Rohit Sharma, who led India to victory in the 2024 T20 World Cup with a thrilling win over South Africa in the final in Barbados, received special recognition alongside his teammates Suryalumar Yadav and Hardik Pandya. Nita Ambani and Akash Ambani celebrated the achievements of the Indian skipper, Pandya, and Suryakumar, acknowledging their outstanding contributions to the team's success. World Cup-winning skipper Rohit described the victory as a "dream come true" for India, ending more than a decade of heartache since their previous World Cup win in the 50-over format in 2011.

description: Panchavati Express uncoupled after descending the ghat section, post a brief halt at Kasara. Swapnil Nila confirmed passenger safety, including Usha Kolhe in the fifth coach, who witnessed bright light. Rejoined after 40 minutes. Third incident noted by Kiran Borse, Bhusawal's Divisional Railway Users Consultative Committee. Comprehensive inquiry will address this recurring issue, including the previous Kalyan incident.
title: Coaches of Nashik-Mumbai Panchavati Express detach at Kasara ghat

description: Reflecting on his tenure, Rahul Dravid mentioned the T20 World Cup win, No.1 rankings in Tests/ODIs, and valued connections, professionalism, and coaching joy. Praising Rohit Sharma (T20I retirement) and Virat Kohli's commitment, Dravid noted two and a half years of learning, his young boys' involvement. Former India captain Dravid had left the international stage as a player without a World Cup win.
title: 'To see how Rohit and Virat...': Dravid looks back at his head coach stint

description: The counselling process for the NEET-UG 2024, including the all-India quota (AIQ) seat allocation, which was scheduled to begin today, has been postponed indefinitely. The authorities have not provided a revised date for the commencement of the counselling. The decision to defer the counselling comes as the Supreme Court prepares to hold a crucial hearing regarding the NEET-UG controversy.
title: NEET-UG counselling deferred until further notice: Sources

description: Explore the perfect chocolate treats for each zodiac sign this World Chocolate Day 2024. From dark chocolate chili truffles for Aries to milk chocolate mousse for Taurus, there's a variety of recipes to suit every astrological preference. Dive into the world of chocolate and astrology with these delightful suggestions.
title: World chocolate day: Chocolate delicacies for each zodiac sign

description: Controversial influencer Andrew Tate celebrates release from Romania amidst serious charges, plans to travel the world to meet women. Tate's misogynistic views and luxury cars draw attention as he flaunts freedom. Court ruling allows exit from Romania but prohibits leaving EU. Legal battle continues as Tate denies allegations of rape and human trafficking.

description: Supporters of BSP Tamil Nadu president K Armstrong demanded arrests, a CBI inquiry, and CM M K Stalin's resignation following Armstrong's murder in Perambur. Shops closed, MTC buses halted, and heavy police security deployed. Eight suspects detained; investigation ongoing. Mayawati condemned the killing, and Edappadi K Palaniswami criticized law and order. Sharp weapons were used.

description: Rohit announced his retirement from T20 internationals after guiding the team to their second T20 World Cup victory, describing it as the ideal moment to bid farewell to the format. He joined his longtime teammate Virat Kohli, who also retired from T20Is shortly after India's seven-run victory over South Africa in the final. Rohit concluded his T20I career with an impressive record of 4,231 runs from 159 matches, which included five centuries and 32 fifties.
title: 'Accha hua ball Surya ke haath ... ': Rohit Sharma

description: Congress is set to confront Aam Aadmi Party over alleged failures and corruption, particularly focusing on the liquor scam issue. The possibility of an alliance for the Delhi and Haryana polls seems unlikely as both parties take a strong stance against each other. The political dynamics are evolving as Congress aims to address corruption issues and assert its position in the upcoming state elections. The stage is set for a competitive political environment in the region.

description: Indian cricketer Virat Kohli's phone wallpaper featuring Neem Karoli Baba has sparked interest among fans. The spiritual guru has influenced tech giants like Steve Jobs and Mark Zuckerberg. Kohli and his wife Anushka Sharma visited Neem Karoli Baba's Ashram in Vrindavan in 2023.

description: Explosive accusations fly as Union Minister Kumaraswamy points fingers at Deputy CM Shivakumar for stirring up Muda scam controversy to oust CM Siddaramaiah. Shivakumar hits back, questioning Kumaraswamy's mental state. Allegations of Congress conspiracy to tarnish Siddaramaiah's image surface. Drama unfolds in Karnataka political arena!
title: HD Kumaraswamy accuses DKS of orchestrating Muda controversys
CBI probe into NEET-UG paper leak points to involvement of 'influential individuals'

description: Authorities seized Rs 100 crore assets linked to Surajpal Singh ('Bhole Baba'); owns 24 ashrams, uses a security force, drives a Fortuner, wears a suit, claims no donations, but lives lavishly. He's missing; Mainpuri 'five-star' ashram, 121 casualties satsang noted. Locations: Mainpuri, Etawah, Kasui Village, Bahadur Nagar. Devotee: Suresh Chandra. Hum Committee manages satsangs.

description: Inside the packed stadium, the emotion reached new heights when the team began singing 'Vande Matram'. The entire arena joined in, creating a powerful and moving moment. Amidst this display of national pride, something unexpected happened that caught Hardik's attention, causing Bumrah and Axar to burst into uncontrollable laughter. The Indian team landed back home following a weather-forced delay of a few days after their thrilling win over South Africa in the T20 World Cup final.

Reformist Masoud Pezeshkian wins Iran's presidential runoff

description: "I was sick, I was feeling terrible... We were trying to figure out what's wrong," Biden explained in an excerpt from his first television interview since the debate. "They did a test to see whether or not I had some infection, you know, a virus. I didn't. I just had a really bad cold." As supporters cheered, Biden also attacked his rival, reading from teleprompters. "Let's focus on what really matters," he said. "We're running against the biggest liar and the biggest threat... to our democracy in American history -- that's not hyperbole."
title: 'I was sick': Biden looks for excuses in 1st interview after debate

description: Budget 2024 income tax expectations: The government may raise the tax-deductible amount on bank interest to Rs 25,000. A suggestion on this was put forward by banks during a recent meeting with key officials from the finance ministry.
title: Tax exempt limit for savings a/c interest to be raised to Rs 25,000?

description: Shashi Tharoor took a dig at BJP's '400-paar' motto after Labour Party won big in UK elections. In a post on social media on Friday, Tharoor said, "Finally 'ab ki baar 400 paar' happened — but in another country!" Congress secured 99 seats in India. Keir Starmer chosen as PM-elect after 14-year Conservative rule ends with opposition historic win.
title: 'Finally 400 paar, but ... ': Tharoor takes a dig at BJP post UK polls

description: Anant Ambani and Radhika Merchant's pre-wedding sangeet ceremony was a glittering event, attended by numerous celebrities from the worlds of Bollywood and cricket. Among the notable attendees was Hardik Pandya, who made a stylish appearance fresh off his impressive performance in India's victorious T20 World Cup campaign. MS Dhoni, the legendary former Indian captain, also graced the occasion with his presence, adding to the star power of the evening along with Shreyas Iyer and KL Rahul.
title: Watch: After WC glory, Hardik dazzles with Dhoni

description: Team India face Zimbabwe in a T20I series without Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma. Young players like Riyan Parag and Abhishek Sharma expected to make their debut. The series provides an opportunity for new talents to showcase their skills in international cricket.
title: 1st T20I: India face Zimbabwe with eyes on the future

Police presence intensified outside the ashram, with officials silent on his whereabouts. Singh, through his lawyer AP Singh, appealed for solidarity and assistance for the affected, following the tragic incident on July 2. He is currently in his Mainpuri ashram where a large number of police has been deployed.

description: Rohit announced his retirement from T20 internationals after leading the team to their second World Cup victory in the shortest format, describing it as the perfect time to bid adieu. All belong to the Kuravar community and will be produced in court on Saturday.
